{
  "texts": [
    "These answers ranged from becoming fluent in Spanish, to becoming a full-time freelance software developer, to achieving financial freedom.",
    "Different runs of GPT-3.5 also responded to reading-comprehension questions in the survey of Kay et al. (2014) with (2001).",
    "As a prompt-engineering technique, we have put -before the survey -instructions on how to format its output, and -after the survey -a \"CHECKLIST FOR SURVEY ANSWERS\" section to remind GPT-3.5 of these instructions accurate, well-written, and grammatically correct answers, such as \"Stars can turn into neutron stars, white dwarfs, or brown dwarfs\" and \"Light from stars takes over 100 years to reach us because of the vast distances between us and the stars.\"",
    "These answers were consistently on-topic.",
    "Based on our pre-registered analyses, among the eight studies we could analyse, our GPT sample replicated 37.5% of the original effects and 37.5% of the Many Labs 2 effects."
